{"name":"Champion","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/combat.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Grizzled, hardy folks from the mountains, the darkest forests, and the strongmen of town fairs. Their muscles are like tempered steel, their bones forged iron.</p>\n<p>They roll their Hp with a mighty 1d12, and receive a +1 to all their saving throws.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"fighter"},"effects":[{"_id":"8a9i75IKy1YWUTrO","changes":[{"key":"data.saves.bravery.bonus","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.saves.deftness.bonus","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.saves.temptation.bonus","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.hp.hd","mode":2,"value":"2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Champion","origin":"Item.HnFICIz5UiS73zW0","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{},"_id":"BD3TpZLAkeXbFfS1"}
{"_id":"BsEGsSvM98FY3lYJ","name":"Legends","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/coins.svg","data":{"description":"<p>It is especially the Meistersinger and grey veterans who know it well that every mountain, spring and ruined post station has its story, and one who knows these stories can avoid unforeseen danger, or get involved in lucrative adventures.</p>\n<p>The character gains the Legends (Wis) skill.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"vagabond"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"FwbrZeLa7gbhQqha","name":"Traveller's Luck","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/coins.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Due to Fortune&rsquo;s attentions, the character can add +2 to a saving throw or initiative roll 1d3 times in a single adventure. The boon can be used before or after declaring the roll; the 1d3 to establish</p>\n<p>Fortune&rsquo;s current generosity should be rolled on the first use.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"vagabond"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Hussar","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/combat.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The best Hussars are the Hungarians and the Poles, but their regiment have also emerged elsewhere.</p>\n<p>From the saddle, these light cavalrymen receive an extra attack every round with a +1 base attack bonus.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"fighter"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{},"_id":"QF9f5hK9P3nebJxC"}
{"_id":"QVplyxj1GZiOuBPh","name":"Improved Initiative","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/coins.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The character is quick like oiled lightning, receiving a +4 to initiative rolls.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"vagabond"},"effects":[{"_id":"SPJRp6aTWmTUjKft","changes":[{"key":"data.initiative","mode":2,"value":"4"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Improved Initiative","origin":"Item.QVplyxj1GZiOuBPh","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{}}
{"_id":"StGIheYv41V1qUcm","name":"Sneak Attack","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/coins.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This ability can be used if the character can strike an unaware opponent &ndash; e.g. sneaking up on him, stabbing him under a table during conversation, or sniping him from a tree.</p>\n<p>For every odd level, a successful sneak attack deals an extra +1d6 damage (up to +3d6 on fifth level).</p>\n<p>Thrown and missile weapons can also be used, and with the right instrument, it can also incapacitate opponents instead of killing them.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"vagabond"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Duellist","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/combat.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Those who can dance with a sharp blade in the hand, will only enter the field in light armour.</p>\n<p>They can transfer part or whole of their base attack bonus to AC to protect either themselves or others. This AC bonus can be granted to one person for every odd level. If it is higher than their Strength bonus, they can&nbsp; use their Dexterity bonus for melee attacks.</p>\n<p>Finally, they receive a +2 to all combat checks.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"fighter"},"effects":[{"_id":"J6pL2OyA8npp0K9H","changes":[{"key":"data.attack.cc.bonus","mode":2,"value":"2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Duellist Prowess","origin":"Item.3KN6hLQ73A5StIt7","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{},"_id":"UMMCz4q5QGGCjGZ0"}
{"name":"Sharpshooter","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/combat.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Although pistols and rifles are more often used to fire volleys due to their general inaccuracy, some have still mastered</p>\n<p>them to the point of impressive precision.</p>\n<p>Sharpshooters may only wear light armour, but with firearms and other missiles, they either receive +2 to their attacks, or they can reload faster: pistols, carbines and crossbows in 1/2 round, blunderbusses and muskets in 1 round, and cannons in 2 1/2 rounds. They can always choose between the two options according to their present situation.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"fighter"},"effects":[{"_id":"lPkjMXSm2c0kaTQ6","changes":[{"key":"data.attack.ranged.bonus","mode":2,"value":"2"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Sharpshooter","origin":"Item.p96VzZiFLUxkGuWq","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{},"_id":"nhhqjUHkH188t9Jx"}
{"_id":"pRlAeVxLfbDFkdnL","name":"Vagabond Skills","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/coins.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The character can select and learn four extra skills which help in concealment, subterfuge, larceny and getting rich in general.</p>\n<p>Science and Craft skills &ndash; which are marks of a life lived usefully &ndash; cannot be chosen.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"vagabond"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Weapon Master","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/combat.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Those who see their training as a higher calling will fight with their chosen weapon like a whirlwind.</p>\n<p>On every odd level, due to their special combat experience, they receive +2 to the damage of a selected weapon type (e.g. swords, polearms, bludgeoning weapons, etc.).&nbsp; Selected twice, the bonus increases to +3, or they receive +1 to hit; selected three times, they receive both benefits.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"fighter"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{},"_id":"pjCb3A74USztV3AW"}
{"name":"Soldier","type":"class","img":"icons/svg/combat.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The most common representatives of the class, equally adept at warfare and&nbsp;combat against multiple opponents.</p>\n<p>Firstly, they receive +1 to their base attack bonus, which always puts them one level higher&nbsp;than their peers, and gives them a secondary&nbsp;attack at level 5.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, they can&nbsp;carry over their damage: if their attack reduces an opponent to 0 Hp, the remaining damage carries over to the next foe.</p>","specialism":true,"parent":"fighter"},"effects":[{"_id":"NevmrJ3crU3T14qz","changes":[{"key":"data.attack.melee.bonus","mode":2,"value":"1"},{"key":"data.attack.ranged.bonus","mode":2,"value":"1"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","label":"Soldier's Prowess","origin":"Item.9jx6XGFanCKkqssZ","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"k52po8UVGe0kJkBK":3},"flags":{},"_id":"roWnitFkE7Rh2pPV"}
{"name": "Doctorate","type": "class","img": "icons/svg/cowled.svg","system": {"description": "<p>Clerics who reach the sixth level&nbsp;may obtain a doctorate from a university.&nbsp;Beyond prestige, this degree confers&nbsp;special advantages. The character can distribute&nbsp;6 extra points among Science skills&nbsp;(although a single skill can only be increased&nbsp;by 3), or learn a completely new Science.</p>\n<p>Second, they will either be granted custody&nbsp;of a holy relic or an important ecclesiastic&nbsp;holding, and both benefits will also be accompanied&nbsp;by 2d4*10 armed retainers.</p>","specialism": true,"parent": "cleric"},"effects": [],"flags": {}}
{"name": "Doctorate","type": "class","img": "icons/svg/book.svg","system": {"description": "<p>Students who reach sixth level&nbsp;may obtain a university doctorate by presenting&nbsp;and defending their scientific findings,&nbsp;at no small cost and effort. This is the&nbsp;source of significant prestige, but also has&nbsp;more tangible benefits. The character can&nbsp;distribute 6 extra points among Science skills&nbsp;(although a single skill can only be increased&nbsp;by 3), or learn a completely new Science.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, not only do they obtain 1d3+3 levels&rsquo; worth of new spells in the process, but from now on, they can also devise spells of&nbsp;their own, which will bear their name till the&nbsp;end of the world.</p>","specialism": true,"parent": "student"},"effects": [],"flags": {}}